oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Photograph of Company 995 Battery S., Parris Island, S.C.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Pvt. Jeff Glynn Montgomery enlisted on October 21, 1918 at Memphis, Tennessee and reported to Parris Island, South Carolina on October 21, 1918, barely three weeks before the armistice. He was discharged in April 1919. Montgomery was from Madison County, Tennessee. The photograph shows Co. 995, Batt. S at Paris (sic) Island, South Carolina.
